{
  "text": "In the knowledge-to-action cycle, after the intervention related to knowledge translation has been implemented, uptake of knowledge should be monitored. [CITATION_1] This step is necessary to determine how and to what extent the knowledge is used by the decision-makers. [CITATION_2] How we measure uptake of knowledge depends on our definitions of knowledge and use of knowledge and on the perspective of the user of knowledge. In this paper, we discuss approaches to monitoring use of knowledge and evaluating its impact, based on a systematic review of the literature.",
